data.name: Sample - Purchase conversion funnel
data.description: This is a sample of how a user funnel could look like. It represents the number of users that performed a specific action at each step.

data.name: Weekly revenue (from Order Completed)
data.description: Shows how much revenue your app is capturing from orders every week. Sales should be registered with an "Order Completed" event.

data.name: Users by browser (last 2 weeks)
data.description: Shows a breakdown of browsers used to visit your app per unique users in the last 14 days.

data.name: Users by traffic source
data.description: Shows a breakdown of where unique users came from when visiting your app.

data.name: Daily Active Users (DAUs)
data.description: Shows the number of unique users that use your app everyday.

data.name: Repeat users over time
data.description: Shows you how many users visited your app for a specific number of days (e.g. a user that visited your app twice in the time period will be shown under "2 days").

data.name: Cumulative DAUs
data.description: Shows the total cumulative number of unique users that have been using your app.
